BHV_Scout
=========

This behavior replaces random scouting with deterministic coverage of the
convex RESCUE_REGION. It records the scout's actual traveled trail and
evaluates rotated, offset boustrophedon routes before every new pass. Candidate
routes are penalized when they approach remembered trail points, so later
passes favor previously uncovered portions of the region instead of reversing
over the same route. Fresh NODE_REPORT data also biases the route toward
territory contested by another scout.

Every SCOUTED_SWIMMER report is immediately sent to the configured rescue
teammate as an offboard SWIMMER_ALERT.

Parameters
----------
  tmate           Required rescue teammate name
  desired_speed   Scout speed in m/s (default 1.6)
  capture_radius  Waypoint capture radius in m (default 5)
  lane_spacing    Coverage grid spacing in m (default 28)
  contact_timeout Maximum age of opponent reports in seconds (default 20)
  history_spacing Distance between remembered trail samples (default 6)
  revisit_radius  Radius around old trail that candidates avoid (default 24)
  revisit_weight  Strength of the old-route penalty (default 20)
